review_blob: Plenty of citrus and some light green onion. Hazy orange pour woth good head and lacing. Bitter finish with some tang. Pineapple. Nice stuff, and still very good despite uncertain age. Bottle.
Pretty nice stuff. Oat and roast worh some chocolate. Light caramel. Black pour with good head and lacing. Pretty bitter finish. Tap at Atlanta terrapin location.
Sharp dark chocolate and good roast. Black pour with great head and lacing. Creamy head on nitro. Bittersweet finish with note of caramel. Tap at airport terrapin.
Easy to drink and boring enough for style. Golden pale pour. Light crisp papery finish. Sampled on tap at atlanta airport location.

Grapefruit peel and plenty of fresh hops. Welcome after a week in Colombia beer desert. Hazy golden pour with decent head and lacing. Bitter finish with a taste of airport smoke lounge. Tap at Atlanta airpirt brewpub.
Mostly just bittering hops here without huge ipa vibe. Golden pour with ok head. Some orange peel. Decent malt backbone. Bottle from Clocktower pub in Cartagena at sunset.

Had a bottle of this on Saturday at the Clocktower plaza in Cartagena. Some florals and a little mash malt. Not bad compared to options here. Golden pour i think, though fmsrank from bottle from supermarket.
UPDATED: APR 23, 2016

Nothing better than drinking trou de diable in Georgia. Word to the motherland. Light florals and some hay. Golden pour with good head and lacing. Light tangy finish with touch of sweetness. Good balance and easy drinking, though not super original. Tap at porter beer bar.
Candied apple and some pineapple. Fresh hops with funky smells. Golden pour with ok head. Light sweet finish. Tap at porter beer bar.

Not hugely into this one. Bretta is a little strong for what Id want a stout to be. Lots of the former. Some roast, chocolate and caramel. Black pour with ok head and lacing. Bitter sour finish. Not a fan. Tap at porter beer pub in Georgia or wherever I am right now.
beer_name: Buxton Special Reserve III Tsar Bomba

review_blob: Roast and subtle caramel. Black pour with good head and lacing. Smooth drinking but not much here. Light bitter finish. Tap at brewpub.
Mostly just sour without any character pertaining to said sourness. Golden pour with good head and lacing. Tap at Porter Beer bar.
Roast and some caramel. Light chocolate and nut. Black pour with good head and lacing. Great balance. Thick, creamy consistency. Tap at brewpub.
Easy drinking schwarzbier. Light roast and a hint of caramel. Some raw barley elements. Black pour with good head and lacing. Crisp and light bitter finish. Tap at brewpub.
beer_name: Wrecking Bar May The Schwarzbier With You

review_blob: Lots of things going on here but doesnt necessarily come together like the regular version. Raspberry and light vanilla. Roast and chocolate. Black pour with good head and lacing. Sweet finish. Tap at brewpub.
beer_name: Wrecking Bar Double-Barreled Raspberry Vanilla Siberius Maximus

review_blob: Very big but properly treated. Lots of whiskey on initial smell - too much for my liking. Then roast, toffee, caramel, chocolate. Oak. Black pour with great head and lacing. Creamy syrupy consistency. Somw booze from barrel. Sweet finish. Tap at brewpub.
beer_name: Wrecking Bar Double Barreled Siberius Maximus Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Lota of caramelized malt and some hint of citrus. A little too sweet for me, though citrus here helps. Amber pour without much head or lacing. Sweet finish. Light syrupy texture. Tap at brewpub.
beer_name: Wrecking Bar Maltlanta Doppel Sticke Altbier

review_blob: Mice and suave. A subtle and well done beer, which is rare for hybrid style that usually tries to go big on either of its bastardized parents. Roast and nice tinge of citrus and bittering hops. Black pour with good head and lacing. Creamy consistency. Some caramel. Bittersweet finish. Tap at brewpub.
beer_name: Wrecking Bar Hopback Mountain Imperial Rye India Black Ale

review_blob: Very good oatmeal porter. Very nice drinking. Caramelized oats and lots of roast. Great balance. Black pour with good head and lacing. Hint of chocolate. Bitter finish with hint of caramel sweetness. Tap at brewpub.
beer_name: Wrecking Bar Sow Your Wild Oatmeal Porter

review_blob: Lots of old school bittering hops vibe here. Lots of citrus peel. Soft carbonation. Orange hazy pour with great head and lacing. Bitter finish. Tap at brewpub.
Light citrus and some oak and resin. A little booze and oak. Dark amber pour with good head. Light tangy finish. Tap at brewpub.
Some citrus and a little vinegar feel. Hazy amber pour. Tangy finish. Ok but not my kind of saison.
beer_name: Wrecking Bar Partition Rustic Urban Ale

review_blob: Nice, easy drinking kolsch. Amber pour with good head and lacing. Great barley profile and a little butter. Crisp finish with hint of tang. Tap at brewpub.
Some citrus and a little pine. Lots of malt. Hazy golden pour. Some bitterness in finish. Decent. Tap at barking dog.

beer_brewer_name: Barley and Hops Grill and Microbrewery
review_blob: Florals and some clove. Dark browb pour with ok head. Light sweet finish. Some raisin. Draft at American taproom.
Lots of fresh grapefruit but doesnt hang together exactly. Hazy golden with good head and lacing. Some malt. Tangy finish with some astringency from grapefruit. Tap at American taproom.
Smoky and sour indeed. Golden pour with ok head. Tangy finish. Some light florals. Tap at pizza paradiso.
Some citrus and some salt and malt. Decent balance. Golden pour. Tangy finish. Tap at pizza paradiso.
beer_name: Amager / Crooked Stave Chad, King of The Wild Yeasts

review_blob: Certainly all it sets out to be. Reminds me of a lot of the stuff JWW is doing. Lots of peanut butter here and some biscuit. Lots of roast and some molasses. Theres a heavy dose of peanut here without any peanut in beer, which Im not sure how they manage. Black pour with ok head. Bittersweet finish. Good, but hovers around a delicate balancing act. Tap at pizza paradiso.
Light tang and salt here. Golden pour with some head. Clean finish. Good for style. Tap at pizza paradiso.
beer_name: Two Roads / Evil Twin Geyser Gose

review_blob: Light coffee and some florals. Hazy golden pour. Light bitter finish. Well balanced. Tap at pizza paradiso

Plenty of rum here with some roast and musky chocolate. Barreling comes on a little heavy here, with lots of boozy aroma. Black pour with ok head and lacing. Bitter boozy and sweer finish. Tap at pizza paradiso.

A bit disapointing from these guys but a very easy to drink light belgian at the end of the day. Nothing huge going on here, but nothing wrong. If all light north american beer was like this it woukd be awesome. Golden pour. Hint of florals. Soft carbonation. Light tangy and otherwise empty finish. Tap at pizza paradiso.

Tastes more like a flanders red than an eisbock but not sure if thats just the menu getting it wrong. Dark brown pour with ok head. Sour plum and some citrus. Some raspberries. Some nail polish vibe and booze. Low carbonation. Some light wine. Tap at pizza paradiso dupont.
Very easy drinking, light gose. Nice to have one that isnt mouth puckering. Light lime and salt. Golden pour. Light tangy finish. Tap at pizzeria paradiso dupont.
beer_name: Nomad Freshie Salt n Pepper Gose

review_blob: Nice citrus and good malt backbone. Good ipa more in the British than american tradition. Golden hazy pour with good head and lacing. Tap at Sauf Haus
Some butter and a little malted barley. Easy drinking but not huge on taste. Golden cloudy pour. Tap at Sauf Haus.
Easy drinking and good for style. Crisp barley and godd ckean finish. Golden pour with good head and lacing. Touch of bitterness. Tap at Gillys.
beer_name: Southern Tier Where The Helles Summer?

review_blob: Citrus and good malt backbone. Easy drinking and well balanced. Orange pour with good head and lacing. Tangy bitter finish. Tap at Gillys.
beer_name: Olivers Balls to the Wall Opening Day IPA

review_blob: Actually works in a screwed up way. Definitely what it says it is. Guava and chile. Amber pour wirh great head and lacing. Spicy finish. Some caramel. Tap at Gillys.
Fine mixture of pineapple and hoppy pineapple. Amber pour with good head and lacing. Some caramel. Bittersweet finish. Very nice. Tap at Gillys.
I think Im guilty of giving this lager a slightly higher rating than a similar macro lager deserves. Am I biased? Crisp and papery. Golden pour. Sampled but not bought at Gillys.
Nice and well balanced. Potpourri and some hint of citrus peel without too much citrus. Golden pour with good head and lacing. Light sweet finish. Nice Belgian strong blonde. Tap at Gillys.
beer_name: Ommegang Game of Thrones #6 - Seven Kingdoms

review_blob: Decent beer - not sure why people roast it so much. Certainly not the best but no drain pour. Florals and a little too much booze. Golden pour. Light sweet finish. Tap at Gillys
Not much here other than a little tang and honey. Very watery. Pink pour. Some citrus. Light tangy finish. Watery consistency and texture. Tap at 7 locks.
Caramel and some boozy rust. A hint of citrus peel. Some florals but a little odd at the end of the day. Reddish amber pour without much head or lacing. Tangy finish wirh hint of oak. Tap at brewery.
Oats and some honey or caramel. Roast. Good even showing for style. Black pour with good head and lacing. Bittersweet finish. Thick creamy consistency on nitro at brewery.
Orange and some light peel. Nice balance here. Amber pour with good head and lacing. Good balance and well done. Rye malt makes for good backbone. Tap at brewery.
Easy drinking and consistent with style. Reddish amber pour with good head and lacing. Some copper and a little cream. Light tangy mash finish. Nitro at brewery.
